BMW Group South Africa has announced that Thilosh Moodally has been appointed as the new head of Mini South Africa. She succeeds Kabelo Rabotho, who left the company at the end of last year. Moodally, a qualified chartered accountant, joined BMW Group South Africa in 2003 in the finance department at the German manufacturer&rsquo;s Rosslyn plant, in Pretoria. In 2006 she joined the BMW Aftersales division and moved to the sales channel development department in 2014. &ldquo;Thilosh&rsquo;s passion, experience and knowledge of BMW Group South Africa and its business, form a solid foundation for her new role at Mini. We wish her success in her new role,&rdquo; says BMW Group South Africa marketing and sales director Lou-Anne Fitzsimons. &nbsp;